text: Vaduz Castle is a castle in Liechtenstein which serves as the home of the royal family of Liechtenstein. It was built in the 12th century by the Counts of Vaduz. It was bought by the Liechtenstein family in 1712. The castle is located on a hill and overlooks the town of Vaduz. Category:Castles in Europe Category:Vaduz
title: Vaduz Castle
